tland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Andreas Heimsamer was born in 1531, in Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Württemberg, Germany, his father, Matthis Heimsheimer, was 31 and his mother, Agnes Agatha Reiser, was 23. He married Agata Reiser in 1557, in Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Württemberg, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died on 26 April 1568, in his hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1531–26. April 1568":"1531–26. aprill 1568","1520–1587":"1520–1587","1531–1568":"1531–1568","1540–1584":"1540–1584","1561–Male":"1561–Surnud","1563–Male":"1563–Surnud","1565–1634":"1565–1634","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","1508–Female":"1508–Surnud","Juli 1563":"juuli 1563","November 1561":"november 1561","1561":"1561","September 1565":"september 1565","26. April 1568":"26. aprill 1568","1557":"1557","1634":"1634","1568":"1568","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1587":"1587","1531":"1531","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","1584":"1584","1540":"1540","1508":"1508","um 1525":"umbes 1525","Sindelfingen, Böblingen, Württemberg":"Sindelfingen, Kreis Böblingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Württemberg, Heiliges Römisches Reich":"Württemberg"},"fi":{"1531–26. April 1568":"1531–26. huhtikuuta 1568","1520–1587":"1520–1587","1531–1568":"1531–1568","1540–1584":"1540–1584","1561–Male":"1561–Kuollut","1563–Male":"1563–Kuollut","1565–1634":"1565–1634","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","1508–Female":"1508–Kuollut","Juli 1563":"heinäkuu 1563","November 1561":"marraskuu 1561","1561":"1561","September 1565":"syyskuu 1565","26. April 1568":"26. huhtikuuta 1568","1557":"1557","1634":"1634","1568":"1568","1500":"1500","1565":"1565","1587":"1587","1531":"1531","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","1584":"1584","1540":"1540","1508":"1508","um 1525":"noin 1525","S